#: ../../../release_details/9.5/multithread-vtkOpenFOAMReader.md:1
msgid "vtkOpenFOAMReader: Multithreaded Reading of case files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/multithread-vtkOpenFOAMReader.md:3
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenFOAMReader` now supports multithreaded reading of case files. This "
"feature is on by default, and it can be disabled using "
"the`SetSequentialProcessing(true)`. It can be useful to be enabled when "
"reading large case files that are stored on a network drive. If the case "
"file is stored on a local drive, it is recommended to keep this feature off. "
"Also `ReadAllFilesToDetermineStructure` has been added, which enables "
"reading only the proc 0 directory to determine the structure of the case "
"file, and broadcast it to all processors. This is off by default, because "
"there is not such guarantee that the proc 0 directory contains all the "
"necessary information to determine the structure of the case file. Finally, "
"several performance improvements have been made to the reader."
msgstr ""
